commit.message: Version 2023.06.19

Revise handling of chunks XML file

Also remove AUTODOC_AbsolutePath
Cleanup PackageInfo.g
Don't build PDF docs if NOPDF env variable is set
CI: drop GAP 4.9 from tests, its GAPDoc is too old
Simplify code using "nopdf" option added in GAPDoc 1.6.3
Update my contact details
Update CI
Version 2022.10.20
Fix more typos
Prevent some file descriptor leaks
Fix typos
Do not try to read non-existing file gap/ContextObject.gd
Version 2022.07.10
AUTODOC_TestWorkSheet: if there is a diff, say in which file
Update tests
Define entities in PackageInfo.g, as a showcase for others
Update CHANGES file
Drop the &see; entity, no package uses it

Output entities into _entities.xml

... which is always generated and is included by the main scaffold page. The
main advantage of this approach is that it allows using entities defined
this way even when using a custom main page.

Note that the generated data is not really XML, so the file extension is
misleading. However, the chosen filename has the advantage that it fits
with the names for most other files generated by AutoDoc, and hence it is
already matched by existing .gitignore rules.
Tutorial: clarify use of PackageInfo.g
Update copyright notice in the manual
PackageInfo.g: link to Mathjax manual by default
Remove superfluous .release script
Version 2022.03.10
Allow AutoDoc record in PackageInfo.g to not contain a TitlePage entry
Strip trailing newlines in PostalAddress and some TitlePage elements
